         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">12 April [1860] ¶ Revd Sir ¶  ¶ I have the hr ¶  to inform you that the gentlemen named in the margin ¶  have been appointed a Board to report upon yr application for a site for a bathing house at S. ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">60.04.12</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Thomas Balmain</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 60/1076, unit 5, pp. 179-80, VPRS 975/P1 outward registered correspondence, VA 669 Department of Public Works, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS is a letter-book copy (p. 179) of a letter addressed to Revd. P. Fenner, Collegiate School, South Yarra. M's copy was recorded on p. 180.</p>
               </note>12 April [1860]<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Revd Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the hr<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">honour.</p>
               </note> to inform you that the gentlemen named in the margin<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Revd P. Fenner; Charles Pasley; J. H. Kay; Charles Ligar.</p>
               </note> have been appointed a Board to report upon yr application for a site for a bathing house at S. Yarra &amp; that the first meeting thereof, at which yr presence is requested, is purposed to be held at Dr Muëllers office in the Btn Gardns at 1 p.m. on Saturday next the 14th Inst</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Sd TC Balmain Secy</p>
         </div>
